Lesson 4: The verb byť (to be) - Past/Present/Future Tenses ===========================================================================================================================================================================
https://slovake.eu/learning/intro/to_be
Past tense:
Singular = Plural
ja som bol(a) = I was
my sme boli = we were
ty si bol(a) = you were (informal/singular)
vy ste boli = you were (formal/plural)
on bol / ona bola / ono bolo = he was / she was / it was
oni/ony boli = they were

Present tense:
Singular = Plural
ja som = I am
my sme = we are
ty si = you are (informal/singular)
vy ste = you are (formal/plural)
on/ona/ono je = he/she/it is
oni/ony sú = they are

Future tense:
Singular = Plural
ja budem = I will be
my budeme = we will be
ty budeš = you will be (informal/singular)
vy budete = you will be (formal/plural)
on/ona/ono bude = he/she/it will be
oni/ony budú = they will be

Lesson 5: Negation ===================================================================================================================================================================================================================
https://slovake.eu/learning/intro/negation
For the verb byť:
ja nie som, ty nie si, my nie sme ...

All other verbs:
ja nemám, ty nemusíš, my nemôžeme, vy nechcete, oni nebývajú ...

1:Ste* zo Slovenska? = Are you from Slovakia?
2:Nie, nie som zo Slovenska, ale z Nemecka. = No, I'm not from Slovakia, I'm from Germany.
1: Bývate v Poľsku? = Do you live in Poland?
2: Nie, nebývam v Poľsku, ale v Litve. = No, I don't live in Poland, I live in Lithuania.
1: Máš dvadsať (20) rokov? = Are you twenty (20) years old?
2: Nie, nemám dvadsať rokov. Mám dvadsaťjeden (21) rokov. = No, I'm not twenty years old. I'm twenty-one (21) years old.

Lesson 6: Grammatical Genders ========================================================================================================================================================================================================
https://slovake.eu/learning/intro/genders
Having flashbacks of highschool french of when I was trying to remember what gender the table(tableau) is - lolympics2024 ~ The west has fallen - Owari Da. Le Fin. It's Over. - パリ症候群 = Pari shōkōgun = Paris Syndrome 
Masculine =  Ten:
 Kto je to? = 	Who is it?
 To je muž. =	That's a man.
 Aký je muž? =	What is the man like?
 Ten muž je vysoký. =	The man is tall.
 To je dom.	That's the house.
 Aký je dom?	what is the house like
 Ten dom je veľký.	That house is big.
Male Words = Ten: chlapec, strom, dom, lístok, autobus, vlak, hotel, pes, hokejista, stôl ...

Feminine = Tá:
 To je žena.	It is a woman.
 Aká je žena?	What is the woman like?
 Tá žena je pekná.	That woman is pretty.
 To je kniha.	That's a book.
 Aká je kniha?	what is the book
 Tá kniha je dobrá.	That book is good.
Feminine Words = Tá: stanica, ulica, kniha, ruža, ruka, noha, hlava, skriňa, izba, mačka, ceruzka, reštaurácia, tvár, pieseň ...

Neuter(Neutral) = To:
 To je dieťa.	That’s a child
 Aké je dieťa?	How is the child?
 To dieťa je malé.	That child is small.
 To je auto.	That's a car.
 Aké je auto?	what is the car like
 To auto je modré.	That car is blue.
Neutral Words = To: mesto, dievča, auto, parkovisko, srdce, okno, centrum, pero, lietadlo, letisko ...

The following question is used for people Kto je to?
The following question is used for animals, plants, objects, and events: čo je to

